sql:
SELECT stock_id
FROM relative_strength_index
WHERE rsi_value > 70;

external_knowledge:
- "Rockstar" stocks refer to stocks with exceptionally high RSI values, indicating strong price momentum; 
- A 14-day RSI value is a measure of the stock's recent price changes to determine overbought or oversold conditions; 
- Outperforming the crowd in terms of average daily trading volume means having a higher average volume than the overall average volume of all stocks over the same period.

sql:
SELECT stock_id, MAX(price) AS max_price
FROM price_data
GROUP BY stock_id;
